reviews.review_text: This is it This is the one to get. The recorded sound the clearest pleasure. Don't hurt yourself with all these "new" tunes. If you were caught late (after 91) by the Grateful Dead these songs are sweet treasures. The only problem is they still leave one wanting more.

Underrated apparently This is a pretty nice aud of what might be the best show of '93. Great versions of the new songs (with lyric flubs kept to a minimum) and tight versions of the rest. I don't keep much 90s Dead on my computer, but this one is on there because it's a great overview of the era.

newsongs...underated agreed here with both previous reviews. This like gold in the golden years of the dead.A really good show over all,mellow song choices for the most part.The sound is very well balanced.Good job taper.
